BT /F2 16 Tf 54 482 Td (6. Backup Strategy) Tj ET
0.85 w 54 462 m 558 462 l S
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 446 Td (The system uses full database backups. Each backup exports table structures and table data) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 432 Td (into a .sql file inside the backups folder. Full backup was selected because it is simple to) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 418 Td (demonstrate, easy to restore, and appropriate for the current system size.) Tj ET
BT /F2 16 Tf 54 391 Td (7. Recovery Procedure) Tj ET
0.85 w 54 371 m 558 371 l S
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 355 Td (- Open Settings, then use the Backup and Recovery module.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 341 Td (- Select an existing backup from backup history or upload a .sql backup file.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 327 Td (- The system validates file type, readability, file size, and SQL contents.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 313 Td (- Before restore, the current database is automatically backed up as a safety backup.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 299 Td (- The SQL statements are executed with foreign key checks disabled during restore and) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 285 Td (enabled again after completion.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 271 Td (- SweetAlert feedback reports success, validation errors, or recovery errors.) Tj ET
BT /F2 16 Tf 54 249 Td (8. Live Demonstration Script) Tj ET
0.85 w 54 229 m 558 229 l S
